369
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:17,660
Hello.

370
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:19,580
Hi, Henry. lt's Charlotte.
ls Sarah there?

371
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:20,860
Charlotte, hi.

372
00:29:20,940 --> 00:29:22,940
Uh... well, she's upstairs
with the kids right now.

373
00:29:23,020 --> 00:29:24,060
Can l take a message?

374
00:29:24,100 --> 00:29:26,700
Oh. Okay. Um...
Then could you just, uh...

375
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:29,940
Just let her know that
l will call her later, okay?

376
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:33,180
Well, l can take a message.

377
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:36,980
Um... well, then, just tell her
that l've got some news, uh...

378
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:40,860
and that l will... l will fax it
to her office in the morning.

379
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:42,140
Okay?

380
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:43,380
Right. Okay.

381
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:45,020
Um... l'll pass that on.

382
00:29:45,100 --> 00:29:47,740
Okay. Thanks, Henry. Bye, now.

383
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:49,220
Bye.

384
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:03,260
That was Charlotte.

385
00:30:03,340 --> 00:30:06,980
She said, um...
she has some news.

386
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:10,260
She'll fax you at the office.

387
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:59,420
So this is it, is it?

388
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:02,340
You kiss the children good-bye,
scribble a quick note, and then

389
00:32:02,380 --> 00:32:03,780
sneak off into the night.

390
00:32:03,820 --> 00:32:06,420
Have you any idea
how fucking cruel that is?

391
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:08,140
l'm not sneaking off.

392
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:10,740
l'm not leaving the children.

393
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:12,900
You could have talked to me.

394
00:32:12,940 --> 00:32:15,580
l mean, writing a note--
it's, uh...

395
00:32:15,660 --> 00:32:18,140
l just thought
it would be easier.

396
00:32:18,220 --> 00:32:19,420
Than what?

397
00:32:19,460 --> 00:32:22,860
Than having
this conversation again.

398
00:32:25,540 --> 00:32:27,580
God, this is so...

399
00:32:34,980 --> 00:32:37,420
l should be back by Friday.

400
00:32:37,500 --> 00:32:39,940
Dinners are in the freezer.

401
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:42,300
Their swimsuits
are in the dryer.

402
00:32:42,380 --> 00:32:44,860
They have swimming
tomorrow at 4:00.

403
00:32:44,940 --> 00:32:47,260
lt's all in the note.

404
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:51,940
l want this to be as easy
as possible for them.

405
00:32:51,980 --> 00:32:53,780
And we'll talk about this.

406
00:32:53,860 --> 00:32:56,940
We'll talk about everything
when l get home.

407
00:34:18,020 --> 00:34:19,580
Sniper!

408
00:34:43,820 --> 00:34:45,940
Oh, God...

409
00:34:49,140 --> 00:34:50,380
This is total carnage,

410
00:34:50,460 --> 00:34:52,180
and not a single western leader
has said a thing

411
00:34:52,300 --> 00:34:53,380
about what's going on here.

412
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:54,780
There's no threats,
no criticism,

413
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:55,900
no fucking comment.

414
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:57,380
This place might
as well not exist.

415
00:34:57,460 --> 00:34:58,900
And now that
we're all they have,

416
00:34:59,020 --> 00:35:00,580
they want us to save face
for them.

417
00:35:00,660 --> 00:35:02,980
Well, fuck that. They should
get off their fucking asses

418
00:35:03,060 --> 00:35:04,780
and get the fuck out here. Shit.

419
00:35:04,860 --> 00:35:06,260
Sorry. l'm still swearing.

420
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:07,700
Freeze it there.

421
00:35:07,780 --> 00:35:09,820
Can we cut?

422
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:19,060
Okay.

423
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:24,220
Roll tape.

424
00:35:24,300 --> 00:35:26,100
Basically, nothing has changed.

425
00:35:26,180 --> 00:35:28,180
People keep saying that
everything has changed.

426
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:29,460
Not from where l'm standing.

427
00:35:29,540 --> 00:35:30,740
Chechnya, Somalia, Cambodia,

428
00:35:30,820 --> 00:35:33,060
Ethiopia--
it's the same shit every time,

429
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:35,300
and it's just going to go on
and on until we stop pretending

430
00:35:35,380 --> 00:35:36,780
that our loyalty ends
with the asshole...

431
00:35:59,420 --> 00:36:01,580
You okay?

432
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:03,260
What do you know?

433
00:36:03,300 --> 00:36:05,500
An English news crew
filmed it six days ago.

434
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:08,060
The sound man is dead,
the cameraman is in a coma,

435
00:36:08,140 --> 00:36:09,380
and Nick has disappeared.

436
00:36:09,420 --> 00:36:11,100
We think it's bandits--

437
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:13,180
Chechens looking for money--

438
00:36:13,260 --> 00:36:15,220
but there's been
no ransom demand.

439
00:36:18,460 --> 00:36:20,580
Sarah, l want you
to meet Bob Strauss.

440
00:36:20,620 --> 00:36:22,020
He's with the lCRC here.

441
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:23,540
He's been helping us.

442
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:27,020
Hi.

443
00:36:27,100 --> 00:36:28,500
No, sit. Sit, please.

444
00:36:32,540 --> 00:36:34,460
So, the, um...
net result right now

445
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:36,180
is we don't know who took Nick.

446
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:37,900
We don't know if he pissed off

447
00:36:37,980 --> 00:36:39,540
the Russians or the Chechens.

448
00:36:39,620 --> 00:36:41,660
We're pretty sure
there was a motive.

449
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:42,740
What was he doing?

450
00:36:42,820 --> 00:36:43,780
l think you know

451
00:36:43,820 --> 00:36:45,940
he wasn't just
a doctor anymore.

452
00:36:46,020 --> 00:36:47,780
He, uh...
l'd have to say--

453
00:36:47,860 --> 00:36:49,500
and this is well known--

454
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:51,860
Nick's activities
went quite a way

455
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:53,380
beyond what you'd call
famine relief.

456
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:54,340
How do we find him?

457
00:36:54,380 --> 00:36:57,260
Well, nobody l've spoken to

458
00:36:57,340 --> 00:36:59,300
has any leads yet.

459
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:01,340
Can we offer a reward?

460
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:06,460
Can... can...
can we do something?

461
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:08,900
The best thing for you
to do is to stay

462
00:37:08,940 --> 00:37:11,060
in the hotel for
a couple of days. Be patient.

463
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:12,900
No. No.

464
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:14,660
No.

465
00:37:14,700 --> 00:37:16,140
Sarah.

466
00:37:17,420 --> 00:37:19,580
Sarah, listen to me.

467
00:37:19,660 --> 00:37:21,220
This place,
they will take journalists,

468
00:37:21,260 --> 00:37:22,660
Red Cross, anybody.

469
00:37:22,700 --> 00:37:24,580
Don't think for one second
that you are immune.

470
00:37:24,620 --> 00:37:26,020
l don't.

471
00:37:26,060 --> 00:37:27,820
Just listen
to what Strauss said.

472
00:37:27,860 --> 00:37:29,500
l don't care what Strauss said.

473
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:31,300
Sarah, l love you.

474
00:37:31,340 --> 00:37:33,540
l want you to be safe. Go home.

475
00:37:33,580 --> 00:37:36,060
l swear to God, l will let you
know if we hear anything.

476
00:37:36,140 --> 00:37:37,020
Say it.

477
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:37,980
What?

478
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:39,060
Say it.

479
00:37:41,740 --> 00:37:44,580
People disappear here;
they don't come back.

480
00:37:44,620 --> 00:37:48,060
l'm not leaving
until l find him.

481
00:37:52,100 --> 00:37:53,500
Okay.

482
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:20,060
Charley?

483
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:23,740
Who is it?

484
00:38:32,220 --> 00:38:33,500
Mrs. Bauford?

485
00:38:33,580 --> 00:38:34,940
My name is Jan Steiger.

486
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:36,420
l'm a friend of Nick's.

487
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:38,780
May l?

488
00:38:41,740 --> 00:38:43,140
We work together.

489
00:38:43,180 --> 00:38:44,900
On and off.

490
00:38:47,060 --> 00:38:49,060
You should move your bed.

491
00:38:49,180 --> 00:38:50,620
lt's too near the window.

492
00:38:50,700 --> 00:38:52,860
Were you working together here?

493
00:38:52,940 --> 00:38:55,620
Yes, in a manner of speaking.

494
00:38:55,660 --> 00:38:56,900
How'd you know where l was?

495
00:38:56,940 --> 00:38:58,260
My sister?

496
00:38:58,340 --> 00:39:00,980
Oh, no, l'm not a journalist,
Mrs. Bauford.

497
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:02,580
l'm more import/export.

498
00:39:02,660 --> 00:39:05,860
Cambodia, we nearly met.

499
00:39:07,180 --> 00:39:08,180
Actually,

500
00:39:08,260 --> 00:39:10,100
Nick mentioned you a few times.

501
00:39:10,180 --> 00:39:11,900
l most certainly would have.

502
00:39:11,980 --> 00:39:13,220
What do you want?

503
00:39:13,260 --> 00:39:15,660
What do you want, Mrs. Bauford?

504
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:17,060
l want to know where Nick is.

505
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:18,940
Last l heard,

506
00:39:19,020 --> 00:39:20,580
he was being held
in the mountains--

507
00:39:20,660 --> 00:39:21,820
a rebel position,

508
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,580
about five, six miles
northeast of here.

509
00:39:23,660 --> 00:39:25,620
Whole area's under heavy
Russian shelling now,

510
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:27,460
but l managed
to make radio contact.

511
00:39:27,540 --> 00:39:29,940
They were negotiating,
they knew who he was.

512
00:39:32,180 --> 00:39:35,020
But that was yesterday,
been nothing since.

513
00:39:35,100 --> 00:39:38,140
Chances are that he's dead.

514
00:39:40,180 --> 00:39:41,540
So why are you telling me this?

515
00:39:41,580 --> 00:39:43,940
l'm curious.

516
00:39:44,020 --> 00:39:46,860
l mean, you come
to this shit-hole in hell,

517
00:39:46,900 --> 00:39:50,140
and you think you can find him?

518
00:39:50,180 --> 00:39:52,100
What is it?

519
00:39:52,180 --> 00:39:53,540
ls this... love?

520
00:39:53,620 --> 00:39:54,940
ls that what it is?

521
00:39:58,660 --> 00:39:59,900
Okay, whatever.

522
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:02,020
You're here.

523
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:03,500
Now...

524
00:40:03,580 --> 00:40:05,460
if l get him back alive.

525
00:40:05,540 --> 00:40:07,860
l'll lose one less operative.

526
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:11,100
lf he's dead, he's dead.

527
00:40:11,180 --> 00:40:14,380
Of course l'm not stupid enough
to risk my own ass

528
00:40:14,460 --> 00:40:16,340
for some fucked-up big mouth.

529
00:40:16,420 --> 00:40:21,100
But you, you're willing
to risk your life for love.

530
00:40:23,940 --> 00:40:26,340
l'll trade with anything,
Mrs. Bauford.

531
00:40:26,420 --> 00:40:28,220
Anything at all.

532
00:40:31,020 --> 00:40:32,060
Fine.

533
00:40:32,100 --> 00:40:35,500
What do l do?

534
00:40:35,580 --> 00:40:37,980
l have a friend, a local.

535
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:40,660
He can get you
into the mountains,

536
00:40:40,740 --> 00:40:43,740
but after that,
l'm just a spectator.

537
00:40:47,260 --> 00:40:49,060
Love.

538
00:42:05,780 --> 00:42:07,420
l'm looking for Nick Callahan,

539
00:42:07,500 --> 00:42:09,780
the English doctor.

540
00:42:44,180 --> 00:42:45,580
Come.

541
00:42:48,660 --> 00:42:50,500
